! Title: No Apple ads
! Version: 20260322.1
! Description: Block Apple advertising on Apple devices.
! Full Adblock syntax for browser extensions (uBlock Origin, AdGuard browser extension, etc.)
! Includes DNS-level blocking rules plus element hiding and cosmetic filters.
! For DNS-level blockers (AdGuard Home, Pi-hole), use NoAppleAdsDNS.
! Information gathered from multiple adblocking forums, Apple official SSL certificates,
! NextDNS native tracking domains, HaGeZi DNS blocklists, and v2fly domain lists.

! ========================================
! SECTION 1: DNS-Level Blocking Rules
! ========================================

! === Core Apple Advertising Domains ===
||advertising.apple.com^
||iad.apple.com^
||iadsdk.apple.com^
||api-adservices.apple.com^

! === Apple Ads Attribution & SDK Subdomains ===
||ca.iadsdk.apple.com^
||news.iadsdk.apple.com^
||cf.iadsdk.apple.com^
||cs.iadsdk.apple.com^
||su.iadsdk.apple.com^
||tr.iadsdk.apple.com^
||ut.iadsdk.apple.com^

! === iAd Content & Workbench ===
||iadcontent.apple.com^
||iadmoo.apple.com^
||iadworkbench.apple.com^
||launch.apple.com^

! === Metrics & Analytics ===
||securemetrics.apple.com^
||books-analytics-events.apple.com^
||axm-telemetry.apple.com^

! === Third-party Apple Ad Domains ===
||iadctest.qwapi.com^

! === Deprecated/Legacy Domains (may no longer resolve but kept for completeness) ===
||banners.itunes.apple.com^
||metrics.apple.com^
||qwapi.apple.com^
||advp.apple.com^
||ls.advp.apple.com^
||proxy.advp.apple.com^
||webproxy.advp.apple.com^

! === iAd CDN Domains ===
||iad-apple.com^
||webproxy-advp.iad-apple.com^

! === Comscore Analytics (used by Apple for ad measurement) ===
||comscoreresearch.com^
||comscoreresearch.net^
||apple.comscoreresearch.com^

! ========================================
! SECTION 2: URL Pattern Rules
! ========================================

! Block Apple advertising pixels and beacons
||apple.com^$ping,xmlhttprequest,domain=apple.com
||apple.com/*/ad^
||apple.com/*/ads^
||apple.com/*/advertising^

! Block ad-related paths on iTunes
||itunes.apple.com^$popup,domain=apple.com
||itunes.apple.com/*/banner^

! ========================================
! SECTION 3: Element Hiding Rules
! ========================================

! Apple.com - Promotional banners and ad containers
apple.com##.ad-container
apple.com##.ad-banner
apple.com##.promotional-banner
apple.com##.marketing-banner
apple.com##.ad-wrapper
apple.com##[data-ad]
apple.com##[data-ad-slot]
apple.com##[id*="ad-banner"]
apple.com##[class*="ad-container"]
apple.com##[class*="promotional"]

! Apple.com - Store page promotional sections
apple.com##.section-promo
apple.com##.module-promo
apple.com##.banner-promo
apple.com##.promo-card
apple.com##.as-promo

! iTunes Web Player - Banner ads
itunes.apple.com##.banner-ad
itunes.apple.com##.ad-banner
itunes.apple.com##.promotional-content
itunes.apple.com##[class*="banner-ad"]

! Apps.apple.com - App Store web interface ads
apps.apple.com##.banner-ad
apps.apple.com##.ad-container
apps.apple.com##[data-ad]
apps.apple.com##.promotional-banner
apps.apple.com##.l-content-banner

! Apple News web interface (if accessed via web)
apple.news##.ad-container
apple.news##.ad-banner
apple.news##[data-ad]
apple.news##.promotional-content

! Support pages - Promotional content
support.apple.com##.promo-banner
support.apple.com##.promotional-content

! ========================================
! SECTION 4: Extended CSS Selectors
! ========================================

! Hide elements containing "ad" or "promo" in class/id (generic)
apple.com##:xpath(//*[contains(@class, 'ad-') and not(contains(@class, 'pad'))])
apple.com##:xpath(//*[contains(@id, 'ad-') and not(contains(@id, 'pad'))])

! Hide sponsored/promotional sections
apple.com##.section-sponsored
apple.com##.sponsored-content

! ========================================
! SECTION 5: Scriptlet Rules
! ========================================

! Prevent ad tracking scripts from loading
apple.com#$#prevent-fetch api-adservices.apple.com
apple.com#$#prevent-fetch iadsdk.apple.com
apple.com#$#prevent-xhr api-adservices.apple.com
apple.com#$#prevent-xhr iadsdk.apple.com

! Remove ad-related cookies
apple.com#$#prevent-set-cookie iad
apple.com#$#prevent-set-cookie ads
apple.com#$#prevent-set-cookie advertising

! ========================================
! SECTION 6: Exception Rules
! ========================================

! Allow essential Apple services that might be caught by generic rules
@@||api.smoot.apple.com^$~third-party
@@||xp.apple.com^$~third-party

! ========================================
! Notes:
! - Apple's ads primarily appear in native apps (App Store, Apple News, Stocks)
!   which cannot be filtered by browser extensions
! - DNS-level blocking (NoAppleAds) is more effective for native apps
! - This filter is primarily for blocking Apple ads on Apple's web properties
! - For full protection, use both DNS-level blocking and this filter
! ========================================
